The World Import and Export of All Goods and Services from 1988 - 2022
================
Nathasya Pramudita
2023-09-20

Is a comprehensive collection of data related to international trade and
trade policies. This dataset is designed to provide insights and
analysis for researchers, policymakers, and analysts interested in
understanding global trade dynamics. It covers various aspects of trade,
including trade values, tariff rates, and trade policy indicators for
numerous countries over multiple years. The source of data is from data
scrapping of [worldbank.org](https://databank.worldbank.org/)

``` r
# Import the dataset
world_export_import <- read.csv("~/Datasets/World Export and Import (1989-2023)/34_years_world_export_import_dataset.csv")

# country code dataset
country_code <- read.csv("~/Datasets/ISO Country codes/wikipedia-iso-country-codes.csv")
```

The data is already clean, there’s no N/A data in important columns,
there’s no duplicate, whitespace, or incorrect data type so I’ll
continue to the next step which is visualizing it.

### Visualizing Export - Import trade around the world

### from 1988 - 2021

``` r
# Creating data frame for global export
world_export <- world_export_import %>%
  inner_join(country_code, by = c("country")) %>% 
  select(country, three_code, year, export = export_per_thousand) %>% 
  mutate(total_export = paste0(country, "\n",
                               export, 000))

# Creating data frame into one for global import
world_import <- world_export_import %>%
  inner_join(country_code, by = c("country")) %>% 
  select(country, three_code, year, import = import_per_thousand) %>%
  mutate(total_import = paste0(country, "\n$",
                               import, 000))

# Creating data frame into one for global growth
global_growth <- world_export_import %>% 
  inner_join(country_code, by = c("country")) %>% 
  select(country, three_code, year, world_growth) %>% 
  mutate(percentage_growth = paste0(country, "\n",
                               world_growth, "%")) %>% 
  drop_na()

# Creating data frame into one for harmonized system table
ahs_table <- world_export_import %>%
  inner_join(country_code, by = c("country")) %>% 
  select(country, three_code, year, ahs_dutiable_tariff_lines_share, ahs_duty_free_tariff_lines_share) %>% 
  mutate(ahs_dutiable_percentage = paste0(country, "\n",
                                     ahs_dutiable_tariff_lines_share, "%"),
         ahs_duty_free_percentage = paste0(country, "\n",
                                      ahs_duty_free_tariff_lines_share, "%"))
```

``` r
# make the font style
font_style <- list(family = 'Retroica',
                   size = 15,
                   color = "black")
label <- list(bgcolor = "#eeeeee",
              bordercolor = "transparent",
              font = font_style)
```

``` r
# The world export map graph
export_graph <- plot_geo(world_export, locationmode = "ISO-3",
                      frame = ~year) %>% 
  add_trace(locations = ~three_code,
            z = ~export,
            zmin = 0,
            zmax = max(world_export$export),
            color = ~export,
            text = ~total_export,
            hoverinfo = "text") %>% 
  layout(font = list(family = "Retroica"),
         title = "World Export\n1988 - 2021") %>%
  style(hoverlabel = label) %>%
  config(displayModeBar = FALSE) %>% 
  colorbar(tickprefix = "$")

export_graph
```

``` r
# The world Import map graph
import_graph <- plot_geo(world_import, locationmode = "ISO-3",
                         frame = ~year) %>%
  add_trace(locations = ~three_code,
            z = ~import,
            zmin = 0,
            zmax = max(world_import$import),
            color = ~import,
            text = ~total_import,
            hoverinfo = "text") %>% 
  layout(font = list(family = "Retroica"),
         title = "World Import\n1988 - 2021") %>% 
  style(hoverlabel = label) %>% 
  config(displayModeBar = FALSE) %>% 
  colorbar(tickprefix = "$")

import_graph
```

``` r
# The world growth map graph
growth_map <- plot_geo(global_growth, locationmode = "ISO-3",
                       frame = ~year) %>% 
  add_trace(locations = ~three_code,
            z = ~world_growth,
            zmin = min(global_growth$world_growth),
            zmax = max(global_growth$world_growth),
            text = ~percentage_growth,
            hoverinfo = "text") %>% 
  layout(font = list(family = "Retroica"),
         title = "Global Growth\n1988 - 2021") %>% 
  style(hoverlabel = label) %>% 
  config(displayModeBar = FALSE) %>% 
  colorbar(tickprefix = "%")

growth_map
```
